                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d285">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">362.1163 Watch Tower/16: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Berlin (<persName type="from">Geist</persName>)
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-27T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 27, 1933—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 27—6:38 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to Department’s telegram of May 15 [<hi rend="italic">18</hi>], 5 p.m.,
                    I made representations last week Ministry Interior on behalf of the Watch Tower
                    Bible Society. Matter being investigated through authorities German states where
                    activities have been forbidden. No decision reached yet. See my despatch sent
                    confidential May 22nd.<note n="56" xml:id="d285fn56">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geist</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
